result.execSummary:
The defendant Chad E Jahn was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Strangulation and Suffocation [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: Fines, costs, and restitution are due during term of supervision.  Court further orders 25% of prison wages to be applied toward Court-ordered financial obligations.  If defendant is released with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment enforceable by all creditors' remedies shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.
Same conditions of supervision as in 16CF7

Defendant Chad E Jahn in court with attorney Mark A. Schoenfeldt.  Defendant in custody. Patti l Wabitsch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Counsel submits plea waiver.  Court examines the defendant as to the plea waiver and finds the defendant guilty.  As to 16CF7, State recommends counts 1 & 3 to be dismissed and read in, count 2: 5 years probation, for count 4: 1 year probation with conditions of No firearms and No Contact with the victim, and 6 months jail time to be served consecutive to time served for 15CF300.  As to 15CF300, State recommends counts 2 & 3 to be dismissed and read in, count 1: 4 years probation with 6 months jail time to be served consecutive to time served for 16CF7.  As to 15CF325, State recommends counts 1,3 & 4 to be dismissed and read in, count 2: 4 years probation with conditions of Domestic Violence counseling and No Contact with the victim.  As to 15CF318, State recommends all counts be dismissed and read in.  Counsel requests to address bail modification.  Court denies motion for bail reduction.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for June 16, 2016 at 03:00 pm.
